node.text:
Is it blue or is it black? One of the questions I get asked most about our island is the color! It’s black, but can take on a blueish hue depending on the light, time of year, and especially with our current blue rug that reflects onto it. Unfortunately I don’t have the color name…if you can believe it when we designed this kitchen with our builder 12 years ago, it was the only black option they had! So I jumped on it. In retrospect, I might have gone with navy if I knew blue would become such a staple throughout our home!!💙💙💙But I do love the black as much today as I did then! Hope you’re all having a great week, I’m sharing a quick summer tour in my stories tonight! We’re getting ready for our getaway to Quebec City soon! We can’t wait!
.
.
Touches of blue and white home decor is always chic and timeless

node.text:
I can’t believe July is almost over, this summer is flying by and I just want it to stay! Who’s with me?? Especially since I think I want to keep this look in our living room for good💙💙💙We’ve been so busy this summer and it won’t be slowing down any time soon for us. I’m away with our daughter this weekend for a dance competition, and next weekend we’re going on a little family road trip to Quebec City! We’re SO excited to take the kids to see the sights and take in all the history! I’ll be planning our trip so if you have suggestions, please let me know! Hope you’re all having a great week, tomorrow is Friday!💙💙💙
.
.
